3  OIDC Onboarding — Primary Pathway (MVP)

OIDC is the default and only MVP protocol. All signups go through this path. The goal is a working OIDC login in under 30 minutes from account creation.

3.1  App Creation Flow

Route: /apps/new — Accessible from Getting Started CTA or sidebar navigation



Step 1  Name Your App

User enters a display name for the application (e.g. "Acme Web App"). App type selection: Public (SPA, mobile — PKCE required) or Confidential (server-side — client secret issued). PKCE is pre-selected and locked for Public type.

Step 2  Set Redirect URIs

User enters one or more redirect URIs. Validation: must be HTTPS in production (HTTP localhost allowed in dev). Minimum one URI required. Post-logout redirect URIs field (optional). Web origins field (optional — for CORS).

Step 3  Configure Token Lifetimes

Access token lifetime (default 15 minutes, range 5–60 min). Refresh token lifetime (default 30 days, range 1–90 days). Scopes: openid, profile, email pre-selected and locked; additional scopes can be added.

Step 4  Review & Create

Summary of all settings. Create App button calls POST /v1/workspaces/:id/apps. On success, navigate to App Detail / Integration page.



3.2  OIDC Integration Page (App Detail)

Route: /apps/:id — The primary developer output. This page must be immediately actionable. A developer should be able to copy values and have working auth in their framework within minutes.



