6  Custom Federation / BYO IdP Onboarding

Custom Federation enables enterprise customers to connect an existing corporate Identity Provider — any OIDC or SAML 2.0 compliant IdP, including Azure AD, Google Workspace, GitHub, or similar — so their employees authenticate using company credentials rather than Foundry IAM-native accounts.

Route: /identity-providers — Workspace sidebar → Identity Providers

ℹ  Keycloak handles the upstream federation protocol natively. Foundry IAM engineering work is the management API, the configuration portal, and the encrypted config storage layer.



6.1  Provider Selection Screen

Route: /identity-providers/new — Step 1 of 5

Display provider tiles with logos — not a dropdown. Visual recognition dramatically reduces misconfiguration. Tile grid layout, 3 columns:



Tile

Protocol

Auto-populated fields

Okta

OIDC Enterprise

Token/Auth/UserInfo URLs derived from domain

Azure AD / Entra ID

SAML or OIDC

URLs derived from Tenant ID

Google Workspace

OIDC (social)

All URLs pre-populated

GitHub

OIDC (social)

All URLs pre-populated

Microsoft (personal)

OIDC (social)

All URLs pre-populated

Generic OIDC

OIDC Enterprise

No pre-population — all fields manual

Generic SAML

SAML 2.0

XML metadata upload or full manual config



6.2  Step-by-Step Configuration Flow



Step 1  Select Provider

User clicks provider tile. System records type. Navigate to Step 2.

Step 2  Enter Configuration

Form fields vary by provider. See Section 6.3 for per-provider field sets. Known providers auto-populate stable URLs. User enters only: domain/tenant ID, client ID, client secret (OIDC) or certificate (SAML).

Step 3 — CRITICAL  Register Callback URL in Upstream IdP

Before saving, display the Foundry IAM callback URL that must be registered in the upstream IdP application settings. This step frequently causes failed integrations if skipped.

Display:

Callback URL: https://id.{domain}/realms/tnt_{id}/broker/{alias}/endpoint

Copy button — prominent

Checkbox: "I have registered this URL in my upstream IdP." Must be checked.

Provider-specific instruction rendered per IdP type (e.g. for OIDC providers: "Add this URL under the allowed redirect URIs in your IdP application settings." For SAML providers: "Register this URL as the Assertion Consumer Service URL in your IdP.")

Step 4  Configure Attribute Mappers

Default mappers shown for the provider type (email, firstName, lastName). User can add custom claim mappings. Table: Upstream Claim (left) → Foundry IAM User Attribute (right) + Sync Mode dropdown.

Step 5  Save & Test

"Save and Test Connection" button calls POST /v1/workspaces/:id/identity-providers. On success, a "Test Authentication" button appears. Click opens the test URL in a new browser tab, initiating a real auth flow against the upstream IdP.



