6.4  Identity Provider Detail Page

Route: /identity-providers/:id



Header: Provider logo + display name + alias + enabled/disabled status badge. Enable/Disable toggle.

Callback URLs section: OIDC redirect URI or SAML ACS URL. Copy button. Provider-specific instruction text.

Test Authentication: Button opens test URL in new tab. Displays last test result with timestamp.

Domain Routing: List of email domains. Add/remove. Users with matching domain auto-routed to this IdP.

Attribute Mappers table: Upstream claim → Foundry IAM user attribute. Sync mode column. Add/edit/delete rows.

Configuration (read-only): Non-sensitive fields displayed. Secrets shown as "••••••••" with Update button.

Danger Zone: Delete IdP — requires typing alias to confirm. Warning: federated users lose SSO and may be unable to log in.



7  Cross-Protocol Field Validation Rules

These validation rules apply across all onboarding flows. They must be implemented consistently in both client-side (immediate feedback) and server-side (authoritative) validation.



7.1  URL Fields

Rule

Applies To

Error Message

Must be valid URL format

All URL fields

Enter a valid URL including the protocol (https://)

HTTPS required (production)

Redirect URIs, ACS URLs, SLO URLs

Redirect URIs must use HTTPS in production. HTTP is only allowed for localhost.

No trailing wildcards on ACS

SAML ACS URL

Assertion Consumer Service URL must be an exact URL, not a wildcard pattern.

localhost allowed (HTTP)

Redirect URIs only

Exception for development — http://localhost:* is permitted.



7.2  Certificate Fields

Rule

Details

PEM format required

Must begin with -----BEGIN CERTIFICATE----- and end with -----END CERTIFICATE-----. Strip whitespace before validation.

Not expired

Parse certificate and check notAfter. Warn if expiry < 30 days. Reject if already expired.

RSA key minimum

RSA-2048 minimum. Warn (do not reject) if RSA-1024 detected.



7.3  Attribute Mapper Validation

Upstream claim: required, max 512 chars, no spaces

User attribute: required, must be a known Keycloak standard attribute (email, firstName, lastName, username) or attributes.* namespace

Duplicate upstream claim: warn if same upstream claim mapped twice — may indicate misconfiguration



