8  Error Handling & Edge Cases

8.1  Global Onboarding Error States

Code

Context

Error

Recovery

401

Any authenticated screen

Session expired

Redirect to /login with return_to parameter

402

SAML/SCIM/Federation

Plan upgrade required

Show upgrade modal linking to /billing

409

App creation

Duplicate app name in workspace

Prompt user to choose a different name

409

SAML SP registration

Entity ID already registered

Show existing SP link; offer to update

422

SCIM enable

Workspace SCIM already active

Show current SCIM config; offer token rotation

503

Keycloak provisioning

Realm creation failed

Retry button + support link. Log to audit_logs.



8.2  Keycloak Provisioning Failure Recovery

If realm creation fails during sign-up (tenant status stays pending, workspace status = error):

User sees a friendly error page: "We could not finish setting up your account. Try again or contact support."

Retry button calls POST /v1/auth/signup/retry with the original tenant ULID

Control plane checks: if tenant exists but workspace status=error, re-attempt realm provisioning (idempotent via Keycloak Admin API)

If second attempt fails: set status=failed, create support ticket in audit_logs with full error context



8.3  SCIM Token Loss Recovery

If a tenant admin loses their SCIM bearer token (cannot be retrieved — stored only as hash):

Navigate to /scim

"Rotate Token" button — shows same once-shown token flow as initial enable

Old token is immediately invalidated on rotation — any IdP using the old token will begin receiving 401 errors

⚠  Document this clearly on the SCIM page: "Lost your token? Use Rotate Token. Your IdP will need to be reconfigured with the new token."



8.4  Federated User Account Linking Conflict

If a user authenticates via a federated IdP but already has a local account with the same email address:

Keycloak triggers the "first broker login" flow

Default behaviour: prompt user to link accounts by entering their Foundry IAM password

On link: federated identity added to existing local account — user is not duplicated

If user cannot remember local password: standard password reset flow, then re-attempt federation

✕  The first_login_flow on identity_providers defaults to "first broker login". Do not change this to automatic linking without explicit customer consent — it is a security risk.



